40#ifndef _NETINET_SCTP_AUTH_H_
41#define _NETINET_SCTP_AUTH_H_
42
43#include <netinet/sctp_os.h>
44
45/* digest lengths */
46#define SCTP_AUTH_DIGEST_LEN_SHA1 20
47#define SCTP_AUTH_DIGEST_LEN_SHA256 32
48#define SCTP_AUTH_DIGEST_LEN_MAX SCTP_AUTH_DIGEST_LEN_SHA256
49
50/* random sizes */
51#define SCTP_AUTH_RANDOM_SIZE_DEFAULT 32
52#define SCTP_AUTH_RANDOM_SIZE_REQUIRED 32
53
54/* union of all supported HMAC algorithm contexts */
55typedef union sctp_hash_context {
56 SCTP_SHA1_CTX sha1;
57#if defined(SCTP_SUPPORT_HMAC_SHA256)
58 SCTP_SHA256_CTX sha256;
59#endif
60} sctp_hash_context_t;
61
62typedef struct sctp_key {
63 uint32_t keylen;
64 uint8_t key[];
65} sctp_key_t;
66
67typedef struct sctp_shared_key {
68 LIST_ENTRY(sctp_shared_key) next;
69 sctp_key_t *key; /* key text */
70 uint32_t refcount; /* reference count */
71 uint16_t keyid; /* shared key ID */
72 uint8_t deactivated; /* key is deactivated */
73} sctp_sharedkey_t;
74
75LIST_HEAD(sctp_keyhead, sctp_shared_key);
76
77/* authentication chunks list */
78typedef struct sctp_auth_chklist {
79 uint8_t chunks[256];
80 uint8_t num_chunks;
81} sctp_auth_chklist_t;
82
83/* hmac algos supported list */
84typedef struct sctp_hmaclist {
85 uint16_t max_algo; /* max algorithms allocated */
86 uint16_t num_algo; /* num algorithms used */
87 uint16_t hmac[];
88} sctp_hmaclist_t;
89
90/* authentication info */
91typedef struct sctp_authinformation {
92 sctp_key_t *random; /* local random key (concatenated) */
93 uint32_t random_len; /* local random number length for param */
94 sctp_key_t *peer_random;/* peer's random key (concatenated) */
95 sctp_key_t *assoc_key; /* cached concatenated send key */
96 sctp_key_t *recv_key; /* cached concatenated recv key */
97 uint16_t active_keyid; /* active send keyid */
98 uint16_t assoc_keyid; /* current send keyid (cached) */
99 uint16_t recv_keyid; /* last recv keyid (cached) */
100} sctp_authinfo_t;
101
102/*
103 * Macros
104 */
105#define sctp_auth_is_required_chunk(chunk, list) ((list == NULL) ? (0) : (list->chunks[chunk] != 0))
106

108 * function prototypes
109 */

111/* socket option api functions */
112extern sctp_auth_chklist_t *sctp_alloc_chunklist(void);
113extern void sctp_free_chunklist(sctp_auth_chklist_t *chklist);
114extern void sctp_clear_chunklist(sctp_auth_chklist_t *chklist);
115extern sctp_auth_chklist_t *sctp_copy_chunklist(sctp_auth_chklist_t *chklist);
116extern int sctp_auth_add_chunk(uint8_t chunk, sctp_auth_chklist_t *list);
117extern int sctp_auth_delete_chunk(uint8_t chunk, sctp_auth_chklist_t *list);
118extern size_t sctp_auth_get_chklist_size(const sctp_auth_chklist_t *list);
119extern int sctp_serialize_auth_chunks(const sctp_auth_chklist_t *list,
120 uint8_t *ptr);

124 sctp_auth_chklist_t *list);

130extern void sctp_show_key(sctp_key_t *key, const char *str);
131extern sctp_key_t *sctp_generate_random_key(uint32_t keylen);

134 sctp_key_t *shared);

165/* keyed-HMAC functions */
166extern uint32_t sctp_get_auth_chunk_len(uint16_t hmac_algo);
167extern uint32_t sctp_get_hmac_digest_len(uint16_t hmac_algo);
168extern uint32_t sctp_hmac(uint16_t hmac_algo, uint8_t *key, uint32_t keylen,
169 uint8_t *text, uint32_t textlen, uint8_t *digest);
170extern uint32_t sctp_compute_hmac(uint16_t hmac_algo, sctp_key_t *key,

174/* mbuf versions */

177extern uint32_t sctp_compute_hmac_m(uint16_t hmac_algo, sctp_key_t *key,
